SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS

  To play BM, you need

     - a 100% IBM PC Compatible Computer with 80386,486 or Pentium processor
     - Miscrosoft Ms-DOS(tm) version 5.00 or better
     - 530Kb of Base Memory (see your Dos Manual)
     - a Vga card with at least 256Kb of Memory
     - a Microsoft(tm) compatible Mouse with Dos driver
     - a 3"1/4 disk drive.

     for the sounds:

     - 256kb XMS memory (Extended Memory - need HIMEM.SYS)
     - a Sound Blaster Compatible Sound Card

     for the music:

     - an Adlib compatible Sound Card

  Note : You can run BM from Ms-Windows(tm) if you don't use the sounds
         & musics but this program is a DOS program !!!


  But Break Machine is a 320*400 MODEX Vga Graphic Mode and we recommand
  the use of :

          - a 486 or better Based Computer
          - a Local Bus (VLB or PCI) Graphic Card
          - a Hard Drive with 1.2Mb Free.

  note : if you're not using a Local Bus VGA Card, some flicker can
         appear and sometimes, the program will run slower.


INTRODUCTION
  In an another dimension exists an incredible World: BRICKANIA
The only thing we know today about this parallax World is his main component
We use to call it : THE BRICK

  Some Bad Monsters Came from this World to Make the Earth a big Wall !

  So, We, the Earthlings, decided to Destroy this Atmospherical Wall.

  The X-PAD 01 ship was especially designed for "Space Bricks Breaking"
  missions.

  But this is too dangerous to put a human in the ship so we employed
  the Best Computer Player, You, to "Virtually" command the Ship.

  The X-PAD 01 uses a new Weapon type called X-Ball but don't let the X-ball
Bounding on earth, we have only 3 negate-X-Ball missiles to protect Earth !

  We will send you some Ship-features to help you but be carreful,
the Brickanians will send you Computer Viruses !

  There will be ugly Brickanian's Monsters and be carefull when you will
reach the outer space regions :

             the very big & violent WormTro'll wait you !

GOOD LUCK !



INSTALLATION

  To Install Break Machine : insert the Disk Labelled "Break Machine" in
  your disk drive then enter :

            INSTALL

  Choose the Destination directory pathname (default is C:\BM)
  then choose then Run Install Command.

  note : The Directory choosed mustn't exist !

You can run the game from the disk but we recommand you to install it because
it will run slower.

CD-ROM distribution Note :

       You can execute BM from the CD but you won't hear anything.



SETUP INFORMATIONS

  Before playing Break Machine for the First Time, enter

         SETUP

  on the Dos command Line in the Break Machine Directory.

  see the SETUP.DOC files for more informations about SETUP.


RUNNING BM

  To Execute Break Machine, enter

     BM

  on the Command Line in the Break Machine Directory

  (see CREATING YOUR OWN LEVELS For more Informations)



USING THE GAME

  Break Machine uses exclusively the Mouse.
  only some Keyboard Commands are available.

  I) MAIN MENU

    If all is OK, after the Game Introduction, you will see a Screen
    with 6 Menu Commands :

              1) Play Game
              2) Game Options
              3) Informations
              4) History
              5) High Scores
              6) Quit Game

    To Choose a Command : put the Center of the IO Logo mouse pointer
    (an i in an O) over the command choosed then click the left mouse button.

  II) GAME OPTIONS

    In this Screen, you can choose:

       - The Digitized Sound reproduction (On/Off)
       - The Fm Music reproduction (On/Off)
       - The Mouse Speed (Low/Med/High)

    then valid your choice by clicking the OK button.

  III) MAIN GAME RULES

    1- newcomer Pilotes

    To Move the X-PAD 01 : use the Mouse. Moving the mouse left will
    move the ship left, to the right : it will go Right !!! (all right !)
    (you can also use the left & right direction keys)

    The X-Ball isn't directly commanded : you have to catch it before
    it disappear at the bottom of the screen and bound on earth !

    The X-Pad 01 is a "directionnal" ship : you can modify the bounding
    angle of the X-Ball (you have to entertain a bit).

    The Objective of the game is to destroy the Wall you see on the screen
    by hitting all the bricks with your X-BALL.

    Many Monsters will come to stop you. their names are:

      - TENTACLE BOB (the Green Tentacle)
      - THE BLUB (the blue monsters with long teeth)

      and in the registered version only :

      - GLOBULA (the awfull liquid E.T. (ha!ha!ha!))
      - Mr SNOW (the carbonic snowman)
      - ROBOCUBE (the connex Robot (Student Joke !))

    You can Destroy the monsters by hitting them with the X-Ball.
    attention : the Ball will go Faster sooner.

    The Final Objective is to Stop the Brickanian's attack based on
    50 easy to "AAARRRRGGGGHHH" Levels. (5 levels in Shareware version)

    Every 5 Levels you will Meet Worm-TRO : the Brickanian Dicator :
    be carefull : every loose will make him more POWERFULL !


    2- Brick Types

    There is 3 different types of brick :

    - The Normal Bricks (blue, orange, green, purple, white, black & red)
      one Single Hit will destroy them.
    - The Tri-Flex Bricks ( gray )
      Three Hits will destroy them.
    - the Transparent Bricks : UnDestroyables !

    note : if you've got the XTra-Ball, you will pass thru all the
           bricks and you will even destroy them (except the transparent one)

    3- Ship Features

      The X-PAD 01 accepts many options :

        the "friend" options:
          - the Laser (L letter) : you will get the famous
            super-protonic Gamme-Ultra Laser class Z :
              "with the S.P.GUL.C.Z. : no more trouble"
            hit the left mouse button to launch a set of 2 torpedoes.
            (the Space Bar will do the same Stuff).
          - the Multi-Ball (M letter) : this will add 2 balls on the
            screen with up to 5 X-balls (this software is a multitasking
            one !!!)
          - the XTra-Ball (X letter) : Powerfull Option : all the X-Balls
            on screen will be featured with an astaunishing protect shield
            that will allow the ball to pass thru the bricks.
          - The AutoPilot (A letter) : 20 seconds of "Do what you want"
            game but you can take the ship control by hitting the right
            mouse button (or Alt Key).
          - The Enlarge Option (E letter) : this Morphs the X-Pad 01 in
            Super X-Pad 01.
          - The Slow Option (S letter) : For Slow people !

            Some Other Features are in Developpement and can appear in the
          game : it's up to you to discover them !

          The "Enemy" Options:
            We don't have any information on this subject !


    4- Keyboard Fonctions

       During the game, you can

              - Pause the Game : Hit the "P" key
                To Continue : Hit the "P" key one more time

              - Quit the Game : Hit the "ESC" Key and confirm by
                hitting the "Y" key.

              - Move the Paddle with Left and Right Arrows.

              - Left Mouse Button  = SPACE BAR

              - Right Mouse Button = ALT KEY


  IV) WORM-TRO DUEL

    When you will meet Worm-Tro, the X-Pad 10 will be Laser - Ready.
    To Succeed : Hit Worm-Tro many times while don't touch his
    Laser Ball.

  V) GAME FEATURES

    Registered Version :

      To reach the End of the Game : you will have to pass 50 levels
      and destroy Worm-Tro 10 times ----- GOOD LUCK !!!

    Shareware Version : only the 5 starting levels are available.



CREATING YOUR OWN LEVELS - Registered Version Only

  You can use your own levels to play with Break Machine, you just have
  to precise the name of the game in command line parameter :

  for example :       enter       BM MONJEU.GME
                      to play MONJEU.GME

  For More Informations : See the BMEDIT.DOC Text File.

  Note : If you play with your own levels : your score won't be recorded
         and 10 levels are only available.


